---
layout: layouts/page.njk
title: "Solutions"
description: "Brunaþéttingar plans, manages and executes fire sealing and technical insulation work on Icelandic buildings — certified systems from Roxtec, Hilti and Promat."
eleventyNavigation:
  key: home-en
  order: 1
heroHeading: "Fire sealing &amp;<br>technical insulation."
statement:
  label: "What we do"
  heading: "Our specialty is <span class=\"ul\">technical insulation and fire protection</span> on buildings — fire sealing, fireproofing, pipe insulation and ventilation insulation."
  lead: "Brunaþéttingar is a specialist contractor in technical insulation and fire sealing, serving contractors, owners and facility operators across Iceland. <strong>We do not offer fire engineering design</strong> — that's a separate discipline. We specifically recommend <strong>Tensio Architects</strong>."
explainer:
  left:
    heading: "What is technical insulation?"
    paragraphs:
      - "<strong>Technical insulation</strong> is the umbrella term for insulation of equipment, building services and structural work."
      - "Where regular insulation keeps heat in the wall, technical insulation keeps it in the pipe, on the structural steel, around the duct."
    chips:
      - { label: "Thermal insulation", style: "blue" }
      - { label: "Acoustic",            style: "blue" }
      - { label: "Fire insulation",     style: null }
      - { label: "Fire sealing",        style: null }
  right:
    heading: "Our services"
    paragraphs:
      - "We provide <strong>complete technical insulation</strong> for buildings."
      - "Our work breaks down into four areas:"
    chips:
      - { label: "Fire sealing",       style: null }
      - { label: "Fireproofing",       style: null }
      - { label: "Pipe insulation",    style: null }
      - { label: "Ventilation",        style: null }
    footer: "We use certified systems from Roxtec, Hilti, Promat, 3M, <strong>Isogenopak</strong> and <strong>WrapTec</strong>."
process:
  label: "End-to-end workflow"
  heading: "From first drawing to final inspection — one team, one process."
  steps:
    - { num: "01", heading: "Fire engineering design",       body: "We do not offer fire engineering design — we work with certified fire engineers." }
    - { num: "02", heading: "Planning",                      body: "Material selection, take-off from drawings and project schedule." }
    - { num: "03", heading: "Project management and install", body: "One crew, one project manager, certified installation." }
    - { num: "04", heading: "Documentation and reporting",   body: "Photo log, location-on-drawing and certification numbers for every seal." }
leading:
  label: "Documentation and reporting"
  heading: "Documentation is the <span class=\"ul\">heart of the service</span>."
  paragraphs:
    - "Every seal we install gets a photo, a location on the drawing and a certification number. The handover report is part of the work, not an afterthought."
  stats:
    - { num: "14",       lbl: "years in fire sealing" }
    - { num: "42,000+",  lbl: "certified seals" }
    - { num: "600+",     lbl: "documented reports" }
    - { num: "100%",     lbl: "inspections passed first time" }
  badgeStrong: "Two report formats"
  badgeBody: "A short handover summary and a full traceability report — both included in every project."
  image: "/img/iceland_karahnjukar.jpg"
sectorsCallout:
  label: "Sectors"
  heading: "Where reliability isn't optional."
  items:
    - { icon: "sector-commercial", heading: "Commercial buildings",       body: "Offices, retail and service hubs." }
    - { icon: "sector-industry",   heading: "Industry and factories",     body: "Heavy industry, plants and processing." }
    - { icon: "sector-hospital",   heading: "Hospitals and public buildings", body: "Strict documentation, no operational downtime." }
    - { icon: "sector-energy",     heading: "Energy and utilities",       body: "Geothermal, hydropower and distribution." }
customers:
  label: "Partners and manufacturers"
cta:
  heading: "Ready to start your project? <span class=\"ul\">Get in touch.</span>"
  primaryHref: "/en/verdreiknir/"
  primaryLabel: "Get a quote"
  secondaryHref: "#contact"
  secondaryLabel: "Send a message"
---
{%- set pillars = collections['featuredServices' + (lang == 'is' and 'Is' or 'En')] %}

<section class="hero">
  <img class="hero__image" src="/img/iceland_svartsengi.jpg" alt="" width="1600" height="900" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high">
  <div class="scrim"></div>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>
      {{ heroHeading | safe }}
      <span class="accent-bar"></span>
    </h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="statement">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div><span class="label">{{ statement.label }}</span></div>
      <div>
        <h2>{{ statement.heading | safe }}</h2>
        <p class="lead">{{ statement.lead | safe }}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="explainer">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div>
        <h3>{{ explainer.left.heading }}</h3>
        {%- for p in explainer.left.paragraphs %}
        <p>{{ p | safe }}</p>
        {%- endfor %}
        <div class="bullet-row">
          {%- for c in explainer.left.chips %}
          <span class="chip{% if c.style %} {{ c.style }}{% endif %}">{{ c.label }}</span>
          {%- endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>{{ explainer.right.heading }}</h3>
        {%- for p in explainer.right.paragraphs %}
        <p>{{ p | safe }}</p>
        {%- endfor %}
        <div class="bullet-row">
          {%- for c in explainer.right.chips %}
          <span class="chip{% if c.style %} {{ c.style }}{% endif %}">{{ c.label }}</span>
          {%- endfor %}
        </div>
        <p>{{ explainer.right.footer | safe }}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pillars">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="pillar-grid">
      {%- for s in pillars %}
      <a class="pillar" href="{{ s.url }}">
        <div class="pic{% if s.data.imageContain %} pic--contain{% endif %}">
          <img class="pillar__image{% if s.data.imageContain %} pillar__image--contain{% endif %}" src="{{ s.data.image }}" alt="" width="1200" height="800">
          <div class="ico">{% include "partials/icons/" + s.data.icon + ".njk" %}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="body">
          <h3>{{ s.data.title | safe }}</h3>
          <p>{{ s.data.summary | safe }}</p>
          <ul>
            {%- for b in s.data.bullets %}
            {%- if loop.index <= 4 %}
            <li>{{ b | safe }}</li>
            {%- endif %}
            {%- endfor %}
          </ul>
          <span class="more">{{ "ui.view_services" | i18n(lang) }} →</span>
        </div>
      </a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="process">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="head">
      <div class="label">{{ process.label }}</div>
      <h2>{{ process.heading | safe }}</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for step in process.steps %}
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="num">{{ step.num }}</div>
        <h4>{{ step.heading }}</h4>
        <p>{{ step.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="leading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="copy">
        <div class="label">{{ leading.label }}</div>
        <h2>{{ leading.heading | safe }}</h2>
        {%- for p in leading.paragraphs %}
        <p>{{ p | safe }}</p>
        {%- endfor %}
        <div class="stats">
          {%- for s in leading.stats %}
          <div class="stat"><div class="num">{{ s.num }}</div><div class="lbl">{{ s.lbl }}</div></div>
          {%- endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pic">
        <img class="leading__image" src="{{ leading.image }}" alt="" width="1200" height="900">
        <div class="badge">
          <strong>{{ leading.badgeStrong }}</strong>
          {{ leading.badgeBody | safe }}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sectors">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="head">
      <div class="label">{{ sectorsCallout.label }}</div>
      <h2>{{ sectorsCallout.heading | safe }}</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="sectors-grid">
      {%- for s in sectorsCallout.items %}
      <div class="sector">
        <div class="ico">{% include "partials/icons/" + s.icon + ".njk" %}</div>
        <h4>{{ s.heading }}</h4>
        <p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="customers">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="label">{{ customers.label }}</div>
    <div class="customers-row">
      {%- for p in partners %}
      <div class="customer-logo{% if p.style %} {{ p.style }}{% endif %}">{{ p.name }}</div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% include "partials/cta-band.njk" %}
